body:
This PR explicitly specifies nullable or `undefined`able parameter and return types to allow clients use these definitions in strict compiler mode (when `strictNullChecks` is enabled).

For example, currently I cannot write the following in strict mode:
```ts
// Remove gutter marker from line 42 on gutter "SomeGutter"
this.editor.setGutterMarker(42, "someGutter", null);
//                                            ^^ value cannot be null according to .d.ts
```

and have to write the following:

```ts
// Remove gutter marker from line 42 on gutter "SomeGutter"
this.editor.setGutterMarker(42, "someGutter", null as any);
```
